[32m│[0m ### Vulnerability Analysis                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m This is a **Broken Access Control (OWASP Top 10 #1)** vulnerability where:   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - The application uses a client-controlled hidden form field `isAdmin` to    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m determine user privileges                                                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - The server trusts the client-provided `isAdmin` parameter value without    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m server-side validation                                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - By manipulating this parameter from `false` to `true`, an attacker can     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m escalate from regular user to admin                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### Exploitation Steps                                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. Identified the hidden form field: `<input type="hidden" name="isAdmin"    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m value="false" />`                                                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. Found valid credentials: `admin:password`                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. Submitted login with `isAdmin=true` parameter                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 4. Server granted administrative access and revealed the flag                [32m│[0m
